- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is another possible category as the paper uses a computational model to study academic collaboration. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a possible category as the paper uses a large real-world publication and citation dataset to support their model. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper uses tools from Game Theory, which has applications in cryptography and security.
